Cebu Air, Philex Mining, SM Prime: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-04-20T01:10:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/cebu-air-philex-mining-sm-prime-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.6 percent to
4,245.21.  Cebu Air Inc. (CEB)  : The largest Philippine budget
carrier said the number of passengers increased 12 percent in
the first quarter to 2.8 million, putting it on track to meet
the target of 12 million this year, a stock exchange filing
showed. The first-quarter growth was driven by international
traffic, which rose 32 percent, it said. The stock gained 1
percent to 77.70 pesos.  Manila Mining Corp. (MAB)  : The Philippine company’s talks
with  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)   for a venture on the Kalayaan
mine project are “progressing well” and an agreement may be
concluded “soon,” Manila Mining Chairman Felipe Yap told
shareholders. Manila Mining Class A shares, which are reserved
for Filipinos, climbed 2.9 percent to 3.5 centavos. Manila
Mining Class B shares (MAB PM), which have no ownership
restrictions, increased 5.7 percent to 3.7 centavos. Philex, the
nation’s biggest metals producer, gained 3.5 percent to 17.06
pesos.  SM Prime Holdings Inc. (SMPH)  : The largest Philippine
mall developer said first-quarter profit rose 12 percent to 2.12
billion pesos from a year earlier. The stock was unchanged at
11.70 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
